<p>We are no longer armies. Not any more. We are animals, trapped in a forest together, uncomprehending. Sometimes, when Volikov sleeps, I hear the Frenchman in the woods, yelling in Hungarian, yelling and laughing. I would almost rather listen to Volikov.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><span class="h2"><strong>9. The Crooked Man | <a href="/scp-783">SCP-783</a>: &quot;There Was A <sup>Cro</sup>ok<sub>ed</sub> Man&quot;</strong> by Shaggydredlocks</span><br />
