<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><a href="/scp-2521">SCP-2521</a> &#8212; ●●|●●●●●|●●|● by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lurkd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1500566); return false;">LurkD</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The most popular format screw on the wiki, and a great jumping off point. All images.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-3999">SCP-3999</a> &#8212; I Am At The Center of Everything That Happens To Me by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2527320); return false;">LordStonefish</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>If you're wondering why the majority of format screw SCPs in this list are from series four, this is your answer. SCP-3999 showed the wiki just how far you can get from a standard SCP purely for the purpose of high-quality writing. Chock full of dream logic and word salad. Rather controversial.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-3043">SCP-3043</a> &#8212; Murphy Law in… Type 3043 — FOR MURDER! by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;">The Great Hippo</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>MURPHY LAW! Stylistically, SCPs are supposed to be analytical and scientific. Lets see what happens when that gets subverted.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-3972">SCP-3972</a> &#8212; &quot;Ken Burns Presents: SCP-3972&quot; by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kate-mctiriss" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1223059); return false;">Kate McTiriss</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;The first person who figures out how to effectively incorporate video into an article, in a way that not only makes sense but is reproducible, is going to walk away from the wiki with like, a thousand million up votes. Mark my words.&quot; -DjKaktus. 3972 doesn't have quite as many upvotes as that, but is still an effective utilization of the video format.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-3939">SCP-3939</a> &#8212; [NUMBER RESERVED; AWAITING RESEARCHER] by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/croquembouche" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2893766); return false;">Croquembouche</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Remember those choose your own adventure books that you read as a kid? This is one of those. Try going through multiple times.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-2439">SCP-2439</a> &#8212; [SLOT UNALLOCATED] by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;">Jack Ike</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Tied winner of the 2016 D-Class contest. For an extra treat after reading, copy and paste the text into a separate document.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-3211">SCP-3211</a> &#8212; There is No Canon by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/croquembouche" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2893766); return false;">Croquembouche</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>This one throws you off balance right from the start, be prepared.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-2786">SCP-2786</a> &#8212; The Archetype by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/billith" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3042342); return false;">Billith</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>There are a lot of SCPs that change over multiple iterations, yet this one stands out due to the effectiveness of its execution.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-3626">SCP-3626</a> &#8212; Do not stop reading this document by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kemot01" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2946390); return false;">kemoT01</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Similar to 3211, this SCP demands a certain level of commitment from the reader. All you have to do is not stop reading it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-3309">SCP-3309</a> &#8212; Where We Go When We Fade, Fade Away by <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lt-flops" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735419); return false;">Lt Flops</a></span> and <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/phamtomguy" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3187915); return false;">PhamtomGuy</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Pataphysics is the general concept that the characters created within a fictional narrative act as real consciousnesses that are aware of the narrative that they are placed within and an authors writing effects them just as it would effect a real consciousness. Be sure to leave a comment.</p>
</blockquote>
